Hi, Lisa.

As Lisa wrote to Dr. Math
On 10/21/2003 at 08:31:21 (Eastern Time),
>[Question]
>If a recipe calls for 5 ounces of sugar for every 15 ounces of flour,
>what part of the mixture will be sugar?
>
>[Difficulty]
>what steps do I take first
>
>[Thoughts]
>15 divided by 5?

This is a ratio problem; you want the ratio

  sugar/mixture

What you've got is

  flour/sugar

Can you see how to find the amount of the whole mixture, and then use 
that in the ratio?


